Dear Justin,

I have been shortlisted for the position 'Research Fellow in Hydrological Forecasting', also in your group, which closed on May 24. However, in my opinion my experience (and interests) may well be better suited to the above position on the FutureDAMS project, which has recently been posted. To give you some context, my PhD research at Imperial College involved regional hydrological modelling of the Indo-Gangetic Plain, and in a subsequent research position I worked on quantifying the contribution of tropical glacier melt to water users in South America. In my current position I'm developing an integrated model of a subbasin of the Ganga river, which includes a spatially-explicit implementation of AquaCrop, as well as a system dynamics model of the catchment to assess how the operation of a barrage for irrigation affects groundwater resources, farmer livelihood and ecological flows downstream of the barrage.

While my initial motivations for applying the first position still stand, I'm minded to withdraw my application for the first position and reapply for the one currently advertised. However, I thought that I would contact you before doing this in order to explain my reasoning, and to ask whether there was a better course of action from your point of view.

